title: Game predictions: Ohio State vs. Rutgers | Buckeye Xtra Sports
text:
Here are the predictions of our experts — and a celebrity chef — for the outcome of Ohio State's game against Rutgers. 

Tim May 
OSU Beat Writer 
The Columbus Dispatch
Ohio State 59, Rutgers 20 
The Scarlet Knights have some offense, but the Scarlet and Gray have more. If Indiana could score 52 on Rutgers, what’s one more TD for J.T. and his pals?
  * * * * *


Bill Rabinowitz 
OSU Beat Writer
The Columbus Dispatch
Ohio State 52, Rutgers 21

With J.T. Barrett running the show, the offense has looked smoother. If the Buckeyes defense can cut down on big plays, this should be a comfortable win.
 * * * * *

Dom Tiberi 
Sports Anchor
WBNS-10TV
Ohio State 49, Rutgers 14 

J.T. Barrett has been given the keys to the car and he is going to drive it up and down the field. Rutgers has a nice offense, but Joey Bosa and company are licking their chops.
 * * * * *

Stanley Jackson 
Analyst for BTB and WTVN-AM
Former OSU quarterback
Ohio State 56, Rutgers 21   

With the captain — quarterback J.T. Barrett — back at the helm, the Buckeyes’ offensive machine, sputtering at times this season, shifts into full gear.
  * * * * *

Mario Batali 
Celebrity chef
1982 Rutgers graduate

Ohio State 42, Rutgers 10  
As a Rutgers grad I’m pragmatic, well-informed and very attentive to social trends. Also, sadly, I’m realistic in my business expectations.
 
  * * * * *
Here are some other predictions from our staff:
>>  Rob Dewolf, BuckeyeXtra editor 
Ohio State 62, Rutgers 14 : Buckeye Nation gets the rout it has been thirsting for since Jan. 13.

>>  Bob Hunter, Dispatch sports columnist 
Ohio State 51, Rutgers 24 : Barrett start good for Buckeyes, bad for Rutgers.

>>  Todd Jones, Dispatch college football writer 
Ohio State 38, Rutgers 20 : The switch to J.T. Barrett makes sense because he’s a better fit for an OSU offense that doesn’t have a deep receiving threat. Look for the Buckeyes to take another step toward the real season that begins Nov. 21.

>>   Rob Oller, Dispatch sports columnist 
Ohio State 52, Rutgers 7 : The old QB switcheroo works wonders, and just in time because the College Football Playoff committee is watching.  #stylepoints

>>  Ray Stein, Dispatch sports editor 
Ohio State 52, Rutgers 21 : With J.T. Barrett running the show, the offense has looked smoother. If the Buckeyes defense can cut down on big plays, this should be a comfortable win.
